WEBVTT

00:00.667 --> 00:01.901
Previously on Underground...

00:01.933 --> 00:04.908
I think I found it,
the way to the promised land.

00:04.933 --> 00:06.234
It's-it's a song.

00:06.268 --> 00:08.837
The map may be hidden in the words.

00:08.869 --> 00:10.838
It's gonna be the slaves
left behind that's gonna

00:10.872 --> 00:13.251
- pay the price.
- Don't act like you care about nobody else.

00:13.275 --> 00:14.509
You only care about yourself.

00:14.542 --> 00:16.376
That's why I don't mean
to be left behind.

00:16.410 --> 00:20.281
Mama, you ever
think about another life?

00:20.314 --> 00:23.051
Yes. I've imagined
thousands of different lives.

00:23.084 --> 00:24.764
You think you're better
than me, don't you?

00:27.770 --> 00:29.130
We have to go. Now.

00:29.163 --> 00:30.258
We gotta run!

00:31.910 --> 00:32.779
Run!

00:32.812 --> 00:34.581
I've never had a runaway before.

00:34.614 --> 00:36.599
If my paddy rollers haven't
retrieved them by nightfall,

00:36.623 --> 00:38.017
consider yourself hired.

00:38.050 --> 00:41.020
Do whatever it takes to get her free!

00:41.053 --> 00:42.021
These are papers,

00:42.054 --> 00:43.589
for you and your daughter.

00:43.623 --> 00:45.066
You can't trust nothing that woman says.

00:45.090 --> 00:46.913
There gonna be catchers on their heel

00:46.947 --> 00:48.595
every step of the way.

00:48.627 --> 00:51.297
There's a price
on your head, dead or alive.

00:51.331 --> 00:53.266
Calling y'all the Macon 7!

00:53.298 --> 00:55.816
I killed her.
I protect my babies.

00:56.502 --> 00:58.724
We suspect there might be
someone aiding runaways

00:58.749 --> 00:59.617
in the area.

00:59.642 --> 01:00.642
Hyah!

01:00.672 --> 01:03.104
Slave catchers are flooding the area,
looking for the high reward.

01:03.128 --> 01:06.113
There's nothing stopping me
from putting you on the block.

01:06.442 --> 01:07.410
What do you want?

01:07.442 --> 01:08.611
I want to be counted!

01:08.644 --> 01:11.213
It's our hands that built this country.

01:13.455 --> 01:15.025
Noah the one
that brought us the freedom.

01:15.049 --> 01:17.736
But he gave up his freedom for me.

01:17.769 --> 01:20.757
Wherever he is, he's still fighting.

01:21.477 --> 01:23.759
All that's behind you now.

01:23.791 --> 01:25.236
No, it ain't.

01:26.127 --> 01:27.796
I'm going back.

